modules.description: This module handles streaming, verification, and construction of Git packfiles using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. It works with entry metadata, configuration settings, and external storage via file descriptors, integrating with types like `Carton.Value.t`, `Carton.Uid.t`, and `Cartonnage` structures. It is used to verify and reconstruct Git objects from a stream, apply delta encoding, generate packfiles, and manage indexing and caching for efficient access.
